TITLE: Implementing a Streaming Genkit Flow
DESCRIPTION: Creates a flow that supports streaming responses to improve UI responsiveness. The flow uses the sideChannel.sendChunk method to stream content as it's generated by the model.
SOURCE: https://github.com/firebase/genkit/blob/main/docs/flows.md#2025-04-22_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
export const streamingMenuSuggestionFlow = defineFlow({
  name: "streamingMenuSuggestionFlow",
  inputSchema: z.string(),
  outputSchema: z.string(),
  streamSchema: z.string(),
})(
  async (cuisineType, sideChannel) => {
    const response = await generate({
      model: "gemini-pro",
      prompt: `Write a detailed 5-course ${cuisineType} dinner menu with descriptions.`,
      stream: true,
    });

    let fullText = "";
    for await (const chunk of response.stream) {
      fullText += chunk;
      sideChannel.sendChunk(chunk);
    }

    return fullText;
  }
);
```

