TITLE: Implementing MCP Server with Custom Tools and Prompts
DESCRIPTION: Complete example of creating an MCP server that exposes custom Genkit tools and prompts. Shows how to define tools with input/output schemas and create prompts with templates.
SOURCE: https://github.com/firebase/genkit/blob/main/js/plugins/mcp/README.md#2025-04-22_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { genkit, z } from 'genkit';
import { mcpServer } from 'genkitx-mcp';

const ai = genkit({});

ai.defineTool(
  {
    name: 'add',
    description: 'add two numbers together',
    inputSchema: z.object({ a: z.number(), b: z.number() }),
    outputSchema: z.number(),
  },
  async ({ a, b }) => {
    return a + b;
  }
);

ai.definePrompt(
  {
    name: 'happy',
    description: 'everybody together now',
    input: {
      schema: z.object({ action: z.string().optional() }),
      default: { action: 'clap your hands' },
    },
  },
  `If you're happy and you know it, {{action}}.`
);

mcpServer(ai, { name: 'example_server', version: '0.0.1' }).start();
```

